    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The unmodificable colletion has a underlying collection that its itself modificable.</p>\n<p>But if you lose the reference for the underlying collection, my understanding is that those two are practically equal</p>\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; doNotTouchList1 = Collections.unmodifiableList(new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;() {{\n    add(&quot;a1&quot;); add(&quot;a2&quot;);add(&quot;a3&quot;); \n}}\n</code></pre>\n<p>same as</p>\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; doNotTouchList1 = List.of(&quot;a1&quot;,&quot;a2&quot;,&quot;a3&quot;); \n</code></pre>\n<p>See this test</p>\n<pre><code>    @Test\n    public void testUnmodifiableLists() {\n        List&lt;String&gt; doNotTouchList1 = Collections.unmodifiableList(new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;() {{\n            add(&quot;a1&quot;); add(&quot;a2&quot;);add(&quot;a3&quot;);\n        }});\n        List&lt;String&gt; doNotTouchList2 = List.of(&quot;a1&quot;,&quot;a2&quot;,&quot;a3&quot;);\n\n        assertTrue(doNotTouchList1.contains(&quot;a2&quot;));\n        assertTrue(doNotTouchList2.contains(&quot;a2&quot;));\n        assertThrows(UnsupportedOperationException.class, () -&gt; doNotTouchList1.add(&quot;a4&quot;));\n        assertThrows(UnsupportedOperationException.class, () -&gt; doNotTouchList2.add(&quot;a4&quot;));\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
